  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency response to escalating humanitarian crisis in Tonj North and Tonj South Counties in Warrap</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will rehabilitate 15 boreholes to improve access to clean water to 7,500 people and undergird this with promotion of good hygiene practices to prevent and reduce diseases. IEC materials will be distributed, including house to house messaging to 20,000 individuals. 1,151 Women and girls will be supported to access menstrual hygiene kits whilst 2,200 households will be supported with WASH NFIs including water collection jerry cans and water purification tablets. This will be implemented in line with the Sphere Minimum standards on WASH.
CAFOD/Tr&#xF3;caire and partner TOCH will provide case management services to GBV survivors. They will receive psychosocial support services such as counselling and referrals on a case-by-case basis and expected to reach at least one hundred sixty (160) survivors. Case management will be carried out in line with Inter-Agency Standing Committee (IASC) minimum standards in emergency programming with an emphasis on the survivor centred approach, confidentiality and adequate participation of women and girls to identify and minimize potential gender-based violence risks.  The project will be implemented in line with the Sphere technical standards on WASH and Minimum Standards for GBV, and Protection mainstreaming.</narrative>
  </description>
